    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing break statement causing unintended fallthrough in UCI handling\n\n### Summary\nIn the `handle_nr_uci()` function within `NR_IF_Module.c`, a missing break statement in the switch case for `NFAPI_NR_UCI_FORMAT_2_3_4_PDU_TYPE` was causing unintended fallthrough behavior. Additionally, a log statement was positioned outside its intended case block, leading to incorrect logging and execution flow.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/NR_PHY_INTERFACE/NR_IF_Module.c`: Moved `LOG_D(MAC, \"UCI handled \\n\");` inside the `NFAPI_NR_UCI_FORMAT_2_3_4_PDU_TYPE` case block and ensured proper break termination to prevent fallthrough to other cases.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain network conditions where UCI FORMAT 2/3/4 PDUs are processed, the fallthrough caused the function to incorrectly execute code paths intended for other PDU types, leading to:\n1. Incorrect UCI handling results\n2. Potential memory access issues due to improper data structure interpretation\n3. Inconsistent logging where \"UCI handled\" appeared even when not relevant\n\nThis issue was observed during high traffic scenarios in NSA mode where multiple UCI types were being processed concurrently.\n"
}